label.value: Union Territory of Andaman and Nicobar Islands

definition.value: A union territory of India. It is located in the Indian Ocean, in the southern reaches of the Bay of Bengal, near Indonesia and Thailand. It comprises two island groups - the Andaman Islands and the Nicobar Islands - which separate the Andaman Sea to the east from the Indian Ocean. These two groups are separated by the 10degN parallel, the Andamans lying to the north of this latitude, and the Nicobars to the south. The capital of this territory is the Andamanese town of Port Blair.

A state in western India. Gujarat borders Pakistan to the north west and the State of Rajasthan to the north and northeast, Madhya Pradesh to the east, Maharashtra and the Union territories of Diu, Daman, Dadra and Nagar Haveli to the south.

A northeastern State of India with its capital at Dispur, in the outskirts of the city Guwahati. Located south of the eastern Himalayas, Assam comprises the Brahmaputra and the Barak river valleys and the Karbi Anglong and the North Cachar Hills. Assam is surrounded by Arunachal Pradesh, Nagaland, Manipur, Mizoram, Tripura and Meghalaya. These states are connected to the rest of India via a narrow strip in West Bengal called the Siliguri Corridor. Assam also shares international borders with Bhutan and Bangladesh.

A State of India. Located on the west coast of India in the region known as the Konkan, it is bounded by the State of Maharashtra to the north, and by Karnataka to the east and south, while the Arabian Sea forms its western coast.

A state in central India, formed when the sixteen Chhattisgarhi-speaking southeastern districts of Madhya Pradesh gained statehood on 2000-11-01. It borders Madhya Pradesh on the northwest, Maharashtra on the west, Andhra Pradesh on the south, Orissa on the east, Jharkhand on the northeast and Uttar Pradesh on the north.

A state in the Punjab region of northern India. It is bordered by Punjab and Himachal Pradesh to the north, and by Rajasthan to the west and south. Eastern border to Uttarakhand & Uttar Pradesh is defined by river Yamuna. Haryana also surrounds Delhi on three sides, forming the northern, western and southern borders of Delhi. Consequently, a large area of Haryana is included in the National Capital Region. The capital of the state is Chandigarh which is administered as a union territory and is also the capital of Punjab.

The easternmost State of India. Arunachal Pradesh borders with the State of Assam to the south and Nagaland to the southeast. Burma/Myanmar lies towards the east, Bhutan towards the west, and Tibet to the north. Itanagar is the capital of the state.
A hill state located in the far north-eastern part of India. It borders the State of Assam to the west, Arunachal Pradesh and part of Assam to the north, Myanmar to the east and Manipur to the south.
A small state in north-eastern India. The state is bounded on the north by Assam and by Bangladesh on the south.
A state in North Eastern India. It shares land borders with the states of Tripura, Assam, Manipur, Bangladesh and the Chin State, Burma.
A state in northeastern India. Manipur is bounded by the Indian states of Nagaland to the north, Mizoram to the south and Assam to the west; it also borders the country of Myanmar to the east.

A state in eastern India. It was carved out of the southern part of Bihar state on 2000-11-5. Jharkhand shares its border with the states of Bihar to the north, Uttar Pradesh and Chhattisgarh to the west, Orissa to the south, and West Bengal to the east.

The northernmost State of Indian subcontinent. Situated mostly in the Himalayan mountains, Jammu and Kashmir shares a border with the India to the south, Pakistan to the west and the People's Republic of China to the north and east. The territory is disputed between Pakistan and India.

A landlocked Indian state nestled in the Himalayas. The state borders Nepal in the west, Tibet Autonomous Region of China to the north and east, and Bhutan in the southeast. The Indian State of West Bengal borders Sikkim to its south.

A state in North-East India. Tripura is surrounded by Bangladesh on the north, south and west. The Indian states of Assam and Mizoram lie to the east. The capital is Agartala. It was formerly an independent Tripuri kingdom [1] and was merged with independent India on 1949-10-15. The state has been divided into 4 districts, 17 subdivisions, 40 development blocks.
A union territory of India.
A state located on the east coast of India, by the Bay of Bengal. The capital of Orissa is Bhubaneswar.

label.value: Union Territory of Dadra and Nagar Haveli

definition.value: A Union Territory in western India. Nagar Haveli is wedged between Maharashtra and Gujarat, whereas Dadra is an enclave lying a few km north of Nagar Haveli in Gujarat. Its capital is Silvassa.

label.value: Union Territory of Daman and Diu

definition.value: A union territory in India. For over 450 years, these coastal enclaves on the Arabian Sea coast were part of Portuguese India, along with Goa and Dadra and Nagar Haveli. Goa, Daman, and Diu were incorporated into the Republic of India on 1961-12-19 by military conquest.
A former French colony, consisting of four non-contiguous enclaves, or districts, and named for the largest, Pondicherry.

The smallest union territory of India. The group is located 200 to 300 km off of the coast of Kerala in the Arabian Sea. The total land area of the territory is 32 km2. Eleven of the islands are inhabited. Lakshadweep is the northern part of the erstwhile Lakshadweepa.
A census town in Jamnagar district in the Indian State of Gujarat.
